Alex seems to hit it well with her, being into the things she likes, such as shows, movies, and even food. However, whenever she presses him on certain questions, she finds that he seems to change the subject, or come up with a reason why he can't talk about it. She doesn't hear about him about many topics about his past, such as where he went to school, his family, or even what he was like as a child. Alex always seems to prefer talking about Lana and his current interests than divulging information about his past. It doesn't come too much as a surprise to Lana, as it seems that is a recurring theme for her past dates and boyfriends, and she tries to enjoy the rest of the evening. They eventually head on back, with Alex wishing her well as he heads back into his apartment. 

As she goes back into the apartment, she ponders whether to continue dating Alex or not. She then hears strange noises, and learns it is coming from Alex's apartment. Worried, she heads out and knocks on his door, noticing it is unlocked. She heads inside, and discovers that bitter truth about Alex. Seeing him changing into someone else, Lana confronts Alex about what she saw. Alex reveals that he is a shapeshifter, and that he has been dating her for the past couple of years. Lana is confused and shocked, which later turns to a strong sense of betrayal as Alex has deceived her all these past years. He tries to explain why he has been dating her, which he claims is because he feels she is his soul mate. Lana understands, but tells Alex why she overall broke up with him in the past. Realizing his secrecy is the root cause for their break-ups, he then promises Lana to be more open to her in the future, and that he is willing to stop hiding who he truly is. Lana after some time pondering, accepts Alex's apology and they both go on to start their relationship anew. While it would take some time for her to trust in her odd neighbor, she is secretly delighted. For once, the person she is dating is completely honest with her, and she feels closer to him than anyone else she had dated in the past, even if it was the same person in different forms.
